<body><div class=WordSection1>
<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>👋 M001 Week 1 — English Worksheet (Beginner)</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> First Hello with the Agent · <strong>Course:</strong> Pyramid Problems · <strong>Level:</strong> Beginner · <strong>Time:</strong> about 30 minutes</p>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Predict 🔮</h2>
<p>Read the steps. Circle your answer.</p>
<pre><code>move forward
place block down
</code></pre>
<p><strong>How many blocks does the agent place? Circle one:</strong> 0 · 1 · 2</p>
<p><strong>Where does the block land? Circle one:</strong> where it started · one step forward · up in the air</p>
<pre><code>turn right
move forward
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Does the agent move the way it started facing? Circle one:</strong> yes · no</p>
<p><strong>Why? Circle one:</strong> it turned right first · it moved up · it did nothing</p>
<hr />
<h2>2 · Find the Difference 🐛</h2>
<p>Clean steps first, then a buggy version. Circle the bug.</p>
<p><strong>Pair A</strong> — Should place a block, move forward, then place another block.</p>
<pre><code># clean
place block down
move forward
place block down
</code></pre>
<pre><code># buggy
place block down
place block down
move forward
</code></pre>
<p><strong>What is wrong? Circle one:</strong> both blocks land in one spot · the agent moves too far · the agent turns right</p>
<p><strong>Pair B</strong> — Should turn right <strong>first</strong>, then walk 2 steps.</p>
<pre><code># clean
turn right
move forward
move forward
</code></pre>
<pre><code># buggy
move forward
move forward
turn right
</code></pre>
<p><strong>What is wrong? Circle one:</strong> it turns at the end, not the start · it walks 3 steps · it never moves</p>
<hr />
<h2>3 · Fill the Gap ✏️</h2>
<p>Place 2 blocks <strong>side by side</strong>. Fill the missing line.</p>
<pre><code>place block down
____________
place block down
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Missing line? Circle one:</strong> move forward · move up by 1 · turn right</p>
<hr />
<h2>4 · Show Your Work 📸🎥</h2>
<p>Switch to your homework world. Build a <strong>4-block straight path</strong> by moving and placing one block at a time.</p>
<p>Record <strong>one video</strong> (a phone is fine). Show two things:</p>
<p><strong>1 · Your code.</strong> Scroll through it. Say what each part does.</p>
<p><strong>2 · Your build.</strong> Point the camera. Name the parts.</p>
<p>Say these out loud, filling in the blanks:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Today I built ______.</p>
<p>I built it using this code: ______.</p>
<p>In this code I used ______.</p>
<p>The hardest part was ______.</p>
<p>That part was hard because ______.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<h3>Submit ✅</h3>
<p>Send this worksheet + your video to teacher on KakaoTalk.</p>
<div class="footer">영어코딩 · <b>english-coding.co.uk</b></div>
</div></body></html>
